## Technical Constraints

- **Performance**: Environment must maintain 60fps on mid-range hardware
- **Compatibility**: Must support major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- **Mobile Support**: Must function on mobile devices with touch controls and responsive design
- **Scalability**: Backend must handle up to 10,000 concurrent users
- **Security**: Implement validation to prevent malicious portal destinations

## Success Metrics

| Metric | Target | Measurement Method |
|---|---|---|
| Monthly Active Users | 50,000+ after 6 months | Backend analytics |
| Portal Traversals | 100,000+ monthly | Backend analytics |
| Registered Games | 100+ after 3 months | Portal registry count |
| User Session Length | 15+ minutes average | Backend analytics |
| Portal Click-through Rate | 30%+ of visitors use a portal | Backend analytics |

## Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: MVP (2 months)
- Basic 3D environment
- Player avatar with simple controls (desktop and mobile)
- Mobile-responsive design
- Core portal functionality
- Initial portal registry

### Phase 2: Enhancement (2 months)
- Improved visual design
- Advanced portal effects
- Developer portal submission system
- Basic analytics

### Phase 3: Expansion (2 months)
- Social features
- Advanced analytics
- Developer API improvements
- Performance optimizations

## Integration Guidelines

### Portal Parameter Specification

For maximum compatibility, games should support these URL parameters:

**Required Parameters:**
- `username`: Player's display name (string)
- `color`: Avatar color (hex code or named color)
- `speed`: Movement speed in meters per second (float)
- `ref`: Source URL of the referring game (string)
- `portal`: Boolean flag indicating portal entry (boolean)

**Optional Parameters:**
- `avatar_url`: URL to custom avatar model (string)
- `team`: Player's team affiliation (string)
- `speed_x`, `speed_y`, `speed_z`: Directional speeds (float)
- `rotation_x`, `rotation_y`, `rotation_z`: Avatar rotation values (float)

### Example URL:
```
https://game.example.com/?username=player123&color=red&speed=5&ref=metaverse-hub.com&portal=true
```

## Glossary

- **Portal**: Interactive object that transports players between games
- **Hub**: The central Metaverse environment that hosts portals
- **State Continuity**: Preserving player attributes when moving between games
- **Portal Registry**: Backend database storing portal information 